description: Test the electrical continuity and switching action of the switch in the control module to verify that it closes the circuit and allows current to flow to the load module when operated., outcome="Continuity of the Control Switch is nominal (R=0.01 Ω), verifying that the switch itself functions correctly. However, the 'Control Output Cable (+)' is found disconnected (floating) at port 'p', which would interrupt circuit continuity. No current flows through the Main Load (lamp) regardless of switch position, consistent with the cable disconnection.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=90.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_switch', 10.0), ('measure_current', 20.0), ('close_switch', 10.0), ('measure_current', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
